#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "Userland Configuration Changes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:113
msgid ""
"man:rc.subr[8] now honors `${name}_env` in all man:rc[8] scripts.  "
"Previously, environment variables set by a user via `${name}_env` were "
"ignored if the service defined a custom `*_cmd` variable to control the "
"behavior of the `run_rc_command` function, for example, `start_cmd`, instead "
"of relying on variables like `command` and `command_args`.  gitref:"
"d15e810db9a5[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:120
msgid ""
"man:init[8], man:service[8], and man:cron[8] will now adopt user/class "
"environment variables by default (excluding `PATH`).  Notably, environment "
"variables for all cron jobs and man:rc[8] services can now be set via man:"
"login.conf[5].  gitref:21c1a93c048f[repository=src], "
"gitref:736a5a6d1dbb[repository=src], gitref:7466dbd68487[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:128
msgid ""
"The kernel now supports enforcing a W^X memory mapping policy for user "
"processes.  The policy is not enforced by default but can be enabled by "
"setting the `kern.elf32.allow_wx` and `kern.elf64.allow_wx` sysctls to 0.  "
"Individual binaries can be exempted from the policy by man:elfctl[1] via the "
"`wxneeded` feature.  gitref:2e1c94aa1fd5[repository=src] {{< sponsored \"The "
"FreeBSD Foundation\" >}}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "Userland Application Changes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:133
msgid ""
"The man:calendar[1] utility again supports nested C pre-processor "
"conditionals and now supports the C++ comment syntax in addition to the C "
"syntax. gitref:19b5c307548[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:135
msgid ""
"The man:calendar[1] utility consistently prints dates according to the "
"locale of the invoking user, not the possibly varying locales of included "
"files. gitref:f1560bd080a[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:137
msgid ""
"The man:calendar[1] utility uses the correct paths for included files if "
"invoked with the -a option. gitref:19b5c307548[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:140
msgid ""
"The man:calendar[1] utility no longer installs data files other than "
"calendar.freebsd.  The data files are now provided by the deskutils/calendar-"
"data port. gitref:d20d6550187[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:143
msgid ""
"The man:daemon[8] utility now supports the `-H` flag to close and re-open "
"the output file when SIGHUP is received.  This permits rotation of the "
"output file via man:newsyslog[8]. gitref:4cd407ec933[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:145
msgid ""
"The man:daemon[8] utility no longer blocks SIGTERM during the restart delay. "
"gitref:09a3675d961[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:148
msgid ""
"The man:devd[8] utility now reports a `kernel` system event when the system "
"resumes from sleep rather than a `kern` system event. gitref:"
"f87655ec7694[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:150
msgid ""
"The man:diskinfo[8] utility now reports the physical device name GEOM "
"attribute when available. gitref:b5961be1ab7[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:152
msgid ""
"The man:elf2aout[1] utility has been removed. gitref:"
"dd99ab06f360[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:154
msgid ""
"The man:freebsd-update[8] utility now displays progress for the \"Fetching "
"files...\" stage. gitref:d6e1e31a0e6[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:156
msgid ""
"The man:freebsd-update[8] utility now supports the `-p` flag, which ensures "
"password db changes are included in [.filename]#/etc/passwd# via man:"
"pwd_mkdb[8]. gitref:9b6591109e8[repository=src] {{< sponsored \"The FreeBSD "
"Foundation\" >}}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:158
msgid ""
"The man:freebsd-update[8] utility now supports the `updatesready` and "
"`showconfig` commands to check for updates and check the configuration "
"respectively. gitref:8cfda118cbd[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:160
msgid ""
"The manual page for the man:freebsd-update[8] utility documents using the "
"`PAGER` environment variable for non-interactive use. "
"gitref:32f4592764d[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:165
msgid ""
"The obsolete version of the GNU debugger installed to [.filename]#/usr/"
"libexec# for use by man:crashinfo[8] has been removed.  Detailed kernel "
"crash information can be obtained by installing modern GDB from ports or "
"packages.  gitref:1c0ea326aa6d[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:167
msgid ""
"The manual page for the man:gstat[8] utility now documents the use of "
"interactive keyboard commands. gitref:cfaa2958dc4[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:169
msgid ""
"The manual page for the man:inetd[8] utility now includes an example of how "
"to use netcat as an HTTP proxy. gitref:a58fc861516[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:171
msgid ""
"The manual page for the man:inetd[8] utility now includes comments for all "
"examples. gitref:26a4a61a285[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "Contributed Software"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/13.0R/relnotes.adoc:179
msgid ""
"The man:bc[1] and man:dc[1] utilities have been replaced by the version "
"developed by Gavin D. Howard.  The new versions do not depend on an external "
"large number library, offer GNU bc extensions, are much faster than and fix "
"POSIX compliance issues of the programs they replace.  They support POSIX "
"message catalogs and come with localized messages in Chinese, Dutch, "
"English, French, German, Japanese, Polish, Portugueze, and Russian.  The "
"previous implementation is still available in FreeBSD-13 and can be selected "
"instead of the new one by the build option `WITHOUT_GH_BC`. gitref:"
"c41fef90a7d[repository=src]"
msgstr ""

